# Code Style

- Prefer readability over cleverness; write code that is easy to scan and maintain.
- Use meaningful names for variables, functions, components, and types.
- Keep functions focused and short; extract helpers when a function grows too large.
- Avoid deep nesting; prefer guard clauses and early returns.
- Keep files cohesive with one clear responsibility per file.
- Remove dead code, commented-out blocks, and unused imports/variables.
- Keep formatting consistent with project tooling and existing patterns.
- Add brief comments only when logic is not obvious from the code itself.
